1
00:00:28,633 --> 00:00:30,600
Manuel! Manuel!

2
00:00:30,733 --> 00:00:33,100
Manong Bert's jeepney is here!

3
00:00:36,167 --> 00:00:37,167
- Please move!
- Dear, will bring you

4
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:38,233
to the hospital, okay?

5
00:00:38,367 --> 00:00:39,533
Please give way.

6
00:00:43,167 --> 00:00:45,167
Dear! Dear!

7
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:46,833
Please give way.

8
00:00:59,833 --> 00:01:00,967
Dear!

9
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:02,600
Manong Bert, let's go!

10
00:01:13,833 --> 00:01:14,867
My child!

11
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:17,467
Andeng!

12
00:01:25,867 --> 00:01:27,667
This doesn't seem
to work anymore.

13
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:30,000
Hang in there, we're almost
at the hospital.

14
00:01:30,133 --> 00:01:31,400
Andeng!

15
00:01:31,533 --> 00:01:33,700
Manong Bert,
please drive faster!

16
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,000
Andeng!

17
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:45,700
Manong Bert!

18
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,300
Love!

19
00:01:51,433 --> 00:01:52,400
Andeng!

20
00:01:59,167 --> 00:02:00,400
Dear!

21
00:02:00,533 --> 00:02:01,833
Bert, why did we stop?

22
00:02:01,967 --> 00:02:02,800
Can't you see that, Manuel?

23
00:02:02,933 --> 00:02:04,833
There's a heavy traffic ahead.

24
00:02:27,033 --> 00:02:28,200
What are you doing?

25
00:02:28,333 --> 00:02:29,733
We can't just wait here!

26
00:03:00,667 --> 00:03:02,267
Please help us!

27
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:03,533
Please help us!

28
00:03:24,100 --> 00:03:25,633
Please help us!

29
00:03:25,767 --> 00:03:27,233
Please help us!

30
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:30,533
Help!

31
00:03:34,967 --> 00:03:35,933
Help!

32
00:03:36,633 --> 00:03:37,733
Please help my daughter!

33
00:03:38,967 --> 00:03:40,333
- Help!
- What happened to the kid?

34
00:03:40,467 --> 00:03:42,733
My child has asthma
she can't breathe!

35
00:03:42,867 --> 00:03:43,833
Let's go over here.

36
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,533
Dear...

37
00:03:47,667 --> 00:03:50,433
Ma'am, Sir,
only one can stay here.

38
00:03:50,567 --> 00:03:52,700
Only one companion
can stay here, Ma'am.

39
00:03:52,833 --> 00:03:54,400
Love, I'll stay.

40
00:04:04,933 --> 00:04:06,733
Update me.

41
00:04:11,967 --> 00:04:14,767
<i>Paging Dr. Mendoza
to neuro ward.</i>

42
00:04:15,133 --> 00:04:17,567
<i> Dr. Mendoza to neuro ward.</i>

43
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:36,100
Bro...

44
00:04:36,967 --> 00:04:38,233
how's everything going?

45
00:04:39,067 --> 00:04:40,733
How's our goddaughter doing?

46
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:50,067
<i> Paging Dr. Fabian to ER.</i>

47
00:04:50,433 --> 00:04:52,867
<i> Dr. Fabian to ER.</i>

48
00:05:05,367 --> 00:05:07,167
Oh, God.

49
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:09,400
Please help my daughter.

50
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:15,300
Please save her.

51
00:05:16,433 --> 00:05:17,967
Is Jeffrey home already?

52
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:20,967
I asked Manang Sita
to look after him.

53
00:05:21,100 --> 00:05:23,067
I also left Coleen with her.

54
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:25,333
Don't worry about them, Bro.

55
00:05:25,467 --> 00:05:26,933
Thank you, Paz.

56
00:05:31,967 --> 00:05:33,900
<i> Dr. Gavino to Area 1.</i>

57
00:05:34,067 --> 00:05:35,500
Andrea's awake now.

58
00:05:35,633 --> 00:05:36,967
Thank goodness.

59
00:05:37,567 --> 00:05:39,767
I'm Dr. Gallardo, cardiologist.

60
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:42,133
So far, your daughter
is already doing okay.

61
00:05:42,267 --> 00:05:43,800
We're still nebulizing her.

62
00:05:43,933 --> 00:05:45,133
But for now,

63
00:05:45,267 --> 00:05:47,733
her breathing has improved.

64
00:05:47,867 --> 00:05:49,167
Thank you, Doc.

65
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:50,667
Oh. See?

66
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:51,933
I told you.

67
00:05:52,067 --> 00:05:53,667
My goddaughter is strong.

68
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,633
It's nothing serious.

69
00:05:56,767 --> 00:06:00,367
But the patient is not
completely out of danger,

70
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:02,267
Mr. and Mrs. Cruz.

71
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:03,500
Why?

72
00:06:03,633 --> 00:06:05,967
The patient is showing
symptoms of a heart murmur.

73
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:11,233
Her heartbeat isn't normal.

74
00:06:11,367 --> 00:06:14,167
Based on the ECG and x-ray,

75
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:15,500
our initial impression,

76
00:06:15,633 --> 00:06:18,567
is that she has
a ventricular septal defect.

77
00:06:20,267 --> 00:06:24,533
It means that the heart's
patient has a hole.

78
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:32,233
A hole in her heart?

79
00:06:32,367 --> 00:06:33,800
How did that happen?

80
00:06:33,933 --> 00:06:35,867
Does your child have
a regular check-up?

81
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,833
It's been quite a while
since the last one.

82
00:06:37,967 --> 00:06:41,600
We are usually able
to manage her asthma attacks.

83
00:06:41,767 --> 00:06:44,667
Her attack earlier was
just so severe.

84
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:47,500
She had difficulty breathing
and felt weak.

85
00:06:47,633 --> 00:06:50,067
She ran around with
her playmates,

86
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:52,533
that's why we rushed her here.

87
00:06:52,667 --> 00:06:55,733
That's one of
the symptoms of her illness.

88
00:06:55,867 --> 00:06:57,767
Doc, what can we do?

89
00:06:58,533 --> 00:07:00,900
To determine the size

90
00:07:01,033 --> 00:07:02,833
of the hole,

91
00:07:02,967 --> 00:07:05,000
in cases like this,

92
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:06,700
we need to perform
an operation.

93
00:07:06,833 --> 00:07:08,867
So we can also close it.

94
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:12,167
If we can do it sooner,

95
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:14,467
<i> it'll be better for her.</i>

96
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,533
<i> You need to be ready</i>

97
00:07:16,667 --> 00:07:20,000
because the operation
is going to be expensive.

98
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:29,800
Where would we get three hundred
thousand pesos, Manuel?

99
00:07:32,733 --> 00:07:35,067
Just for Andrea's
medication alone,

100
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:36,767
our money is not even enough.

101
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:40,900
What about our daily expenses?

102
00:07:41,033 --> 00:07:44,267
The house, food,

103
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:46,033
water, electricity,

104
00:07:46,167 --> 00:07:51,633
our payment for the house,
and our baby's milk?

105
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:56,833
What about Jeffrey's school
supplies?

106
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:00,767
What if I work abroad?

107
00:08:04,333 --> 00:08:06,633
Abel has been asking me
to go with him.

108
00:08:10,933 --> 00:08:11,833
What?

109
00:08:15,467 --> 00:08:17,733
Love, haven't we talked about
this already?

110
00:08:18,967 --> 00:08:22,600
We'll stay together
no matter what happens.

111
00:08:22,767 --> 00:08:24,967
But the situation
is different now.

112
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:27,533
Our daughter is sick.

113
00:08:27,667 --> 00:08:29,333
Love, even if I worked overtime,

114
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:31,400
I couldn't earn that amount
of money.

115
00:08:31,533 --> 00:08:34,567
You know the salary of a janitor
in our country.

116
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:36,000
Then...

117
00:08:36,133 --> 00:08:37,300
I'll help you!

118
00:08:39,033 --> 00:08:41,233
Aside from<i> longganisa</i> ,

119
00:08:41,367 --> 00:08:44,267
I'll also make<i> tocino</i> and<i> tapa</i> .

120
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:46,833
And I'll ask Paz

121
00:08:46,967 --> 00:08:49,333
to help me sell them.

122
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:51,767
I'll work part-time

123
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:53,800
so you don't have to go.

124
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:59,267
Love, I'm not
underestimating it, okay?

125
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:01,200
How much would you earn
from that?

126
00:09:02,067 --> 00:09:04,300
It's still not enough
for Andrea's operation.

127
00:09:04,433 --> 00:09:06,867
<i> Paging Dr. Fabian to ER.</i>

128
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,400
<i> Dr. Fabian to ER.</i>

129
00:09:08,533 --> 00:09:10,133
Maybe these things
are happening...

130
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:13,933
because God is punishing us.

131
00:09:16,367 --> 00:09:17,833
Because up until now,
our relationship

132
00:09:17,967 --> 00:09:19,033
still isn't blessed.

133
00:09:20,533 --> 00:09:21,700
Love...

134
00:09:23,267 --> 00:09:25,800
are we really going
to talk about marriage now?

135
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:28,467
Let's do that later.

136
00:09:28,633 --> 00:09:30,467
Let's focus on Andrea for now.

137
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:40,067
What if...

138
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:42,233
we get a loan?

139
00:09:43,633 --> 00:09:44,867
From whom?

140
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:45,967
Where?

141
00:09:47,233 --> 00:09:50,200
And how would we pay that?

142
00:09:50,333 --> 00:09:53,000
We're already struggling
to make ends meet.

143
00:09:53,133 --> 00:09:54,933
What will happen
if we get a loan?

144
00:09:57,867 --> 00:09:59,667
Love...

145
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:01,367
I don't want us
to part ways either,

146
00:10:01,533 --> 00:10:02,800
but...

147
00:10:02,933 --> 00:10:05,833
for our daughter's sake,
I'm willing to make sacrifices.

148
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,967
I'm also willing
to make sacrifices.

149
00:10:09,867 --> 00:10:11,233
You know that.

150
00:10:11,367 --> 00:10:12,967
So, let me do it.

151
00:10:14,367 --> 00:10:16,500
Abel is flying back
to Saudi soon.

152
00:10:17,433 --> 00:10:18,900
Maybe I can go with him.

153
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:21,700
Love, he said...

154
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:23,500
I will earn triple my salary.

155
00:10:24,933 --> 00:10:27,933
We'll save money faster
for our daughter.

156
00:10:51,367 --> 00:10:52,867
You're leaving?

157
00:10:56,867 --> 00:10:58,567
Dear...

158
00:10:58,700 --> 00:11:00,767
I'm doing this for you.

159
00:11:01,467 --> 00:11:03,567
So we can afford your operation.

160
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:06,133
But didn't the doctor say

161
00:11:06,267 --> 00:11:11,400
if she avoids playing too much
and tiring herself?

162
00:11:11,567 --> 00:11:13,400
It's okay not to proceed
with the operation?

163
00:11:16,367 --> 00:11:18,067
He's right, Dad.

164
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:20,867
I promise,
I won't run anymore.

165
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,900
I'll try not to push myself
too hard anymore.

166
00:11:24,033 --> 00:11:26,233
So I don't have to undergo
an operation.

167
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:28,767
So that you don't have to leave.

168
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:31,033
I won't ask for new shoes.

169
00:11:32,733 --> 00:11:34,667
Let's just get this fixed.

170
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:36,733
Let's save the money for Andrea.

171
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,900
Dear...

172
00:11:42,067 --> 00:11:44,367
my contract won't be too long.

173
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:46,267
Two years will pass by quickly.

174
00:11:47,267 --> 00:11:49,433
I'll go home once
I have enough savings.

175
00:11:54,467 --> 00:11:56,867
You heard what
your dad said, right?

176
00:11:58,833 --> 00:12:02,833
Just think about
Andrea's operation.

177
00:12:05,833 --> 00:12:07,367
You'll get better soon, Dear,

178
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:09,267
and you can play again.

179
00:12:09,900 --> 00:12:11,267
When it happens...

180
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,333
your dad won't have
to leave again.

181
00:12:13,467 --> 00:12:15,133
Yes, I'll stay here.

182
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:16,767
We'll stay together forever.

183
00:12:17,633 --> 00:12:19,533
I promise.

184
00:12:52,167 --> 00:12:55,067
Darling, call us right away

185
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:56,833
once the plane lands, okay?

186
00:12:56,967 --> 00:12:58,867
So we'll know that
you're safe. Okay?

187
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:01,533
Of course. Take care
of yourselves, too, okay?

188
00:13:01,667 --> 00:13:02,833
Be safe.

189
00:13:02,967 --> 00:13:04,033
Your favorite.

190
00:13:05,033 --> 00:13:07,600
Looks like it'll take some time
before I can cook for you again.

191
00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:09,767
Come on.
I'm still here,

192
00:13:09,900 --> 00:13:11,433
and you're already
making me miss you.

193
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:14,867
What if you miss us?

194
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:16,133
Miss me?

195
00:13:16,267 --> 00:13:17,533
Sooner or later,

196
00:13:17,667 --> 00:13:19,733
you're going to look
at other women.

197
00:13:19,867 --> 00:13:21,267
What are you talking about?

198
00:13:22,533 --> 00:13:23,333
You're beautiful.

199
00:13:23,467 --> 00:13:24,733
Why would I need to look
at other women?

200
00:13:26,567 --> 00:13:29,367
You're the only woman
in my life, Love.

201
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:30,367
You know that.

202
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:32,533
- Yes.
- Really? Promise?

203
00:13:32,933 --> 00:13:33,933
Promise.

204
00:13:39,133 --> 00:13:40,400
That's you, Dad.

205
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:42,300
This is me.

206
00:13:43,467 --> 00:13:46,367
This is mom, holding Coleen.

207
00:13:47,433 --> 00:13:48,767
And big brother Jeffrey.

208
00:13:49,467 --> 00:13:53,033
Look at it whenever you miss us.

209
00:13:57,300 --> 00:13:58,400
Thank you, Dear.

210
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:00,567
Be a good girl.

211
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:04,100
Always bring your inhaler.

212
00:14:05,700 --> 00:14:07,867
Take a rest whenever
you're having an asthma attack.

213
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:11,233
To prevent your heart
from getting worst.

214
00:14:18,700 --> 00:14:19,667
Have this, Dad.

215
00:14:22,267 --> 00:14:23,767
Don't remove it, okay?

216
00:14:24,233 --> 00:14:26,367
So you won't forget me.

217
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:27,567
Jeffrey, you'll be
the one holding

218
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:29,400
the family together for now.

219
00:14:29,567 --> 00:14:31,367
You'll have to help your mom...

220
00:14:32,333 --> 00:14:33,700
and your siblings.

221
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:37,967
Take good care of them,
do you understand?

222
00:14:38,100 --> 00:14:39,633
Yes, Dad.

223
00:14:39,767 --> 00:14:42,167
And don't give your mom
a problem.

224
00:14:42,300 --> 00:14:44,033
Don't fight, okay?

225
00:14:44,167 --> 00:14:45,167
Yes, Dad.

226
00:14:46,267 --> 00:14:48,100
Bro, we need to go.

227
00:14:48,233 --> 00:14:49,367
Okay, let's go.

228
00:14:52,367 --> 00:14:53,833
Kiss now.

229
00:14:53,967 --> 00:14:55,333
Friend, come on.

230
00:14:55,467 --> 00:14:57,133
Hey, Sister. What is that?

231
00:14:57,267 --> 00:14:59,767
They might miss their flight.

232
00:15:06,833 --> 00:15:07,800
Dad.

233
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:16,767
Dad!

234
00:15:17,967 --> 00:15:20,033
Come on. Don't cry.

235
00:15:20,167 --> 00:15:21,767
That's not good for you.

236
00:15:21,900 --> 00:15:22,867
That's enough. Stop.

237
00:15:23,933 --> 00:15:24,900
Stop.

238
00:15:25,667 --> 00:15:28,400
I promise, I'll go home soon.

239
00:15:35,233 --> 00:15:36,600
Dear, that's enough.

240
00:15:36,733 --> 00:15:38,300
Your dad will be late.

241
00:15:39,867 --> 00:15:41,333
Take care always.

242
00:15:41,467 --> 00:15:42,800
Love! Be safe.

243
00:16:16,867 --> 00:16:18,067
Hello.

244
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:20,733
Hey. Hi.

245
00:16:21,067 --> 00:16:22,567
Hazel, here's what
you asked me to get for you.

246
00:16:22,700 --> 00:16:23,867
Thank you.

247
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:25,667
I can't go down
to the cafeteria.

248
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:26,833
I'm sorry for the bother.

249
00:16:26,967 --> 00:16:28,200
It's okay.

250
00:16:30,967 --> 00:16:32,833
Manuel is hardworking.

251
00:16:32,967 --> 00:16:34,767
- Who?
- Manuel.

252
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:37,867
Hardworking.

253
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,733
Alright then, I'll return
to the ER now.

254
00:16:39,867 --> 00:16:40,733
Okay, then.

255
00:16:40,867 --> 00:16:41,900
Could you bring this
to the nurse station?

256
00:16:42,067 --> 00:16:43,033
- Sure.
- I'll go down there.

257
00:16:43,167 --> 00:16:44,733
- It's okay.
- Okay. Thank you.

258
00:16:57,467 --> 00:16:58,400
Sir?

259
00:17:00,567 --> 00:17:02,100
Are you okay?

260
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:04,667
Sir? Are you...

261
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:06,633
Sir! Oh, no!

262
00:17:06,767 --> 00:17:07,800
Sir.

263
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:10,533
Please, please.

264
00:17:10,667 --> 00:17:12,633
Okay. Please relax.

265
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:14,233
Are you okay?

266
00:17:17,033 --> 00:17:17,833
- Yes?
- Peace be with you.

267
00:17:17,967 --> 00:17:19,167
Ma'am, looks like he threw up.

268
00:17:19,300 --> 00:17:20,500
- I'll have it cleaned
- Yes.

269
00:17:20,633 --> 00:17:22,067
Okay, Thank you.

270
00:17:24,967 --> 00:17:27,000
Okay, take it easy.

271
00:17:27,133 --> 00:17:28,267
Just relax.

272
00:17:44,300 --> 00:17:46,100
Where's Baby Coleen?

273
00:17:46,233 --> 00:17:48,400
<i> I left her in Paz's care.</i>

274
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:50,000
<i> She fell asleep.</i>

275
00:17:50,133 --> 00:17:51,267
How are you doing, Love?

276
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:52,433
We're doing okay.

277
00:17:52,567 --> 00:17:55,133
I received the money you
sent us.

278
00:17:55,267 --> 00:17:57,533
<i> I bought Andrea's medicine</i>

279
00:17:57,667 --> 00:18:00,933
And I saved some of
the money for her operation.

280
00:18:02,100 --> 00:18:03,633
I'm glad to hear that.

281
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:06,767
How are you, Andeng?

282
00:18:06,900 --> 00:18:07,933
I'm a good girl.

283
00:18:08,067 --> 00:18:09,467
Mayette and I don't run.

284
00:18:10,467 --> 00:18:11,433
Really?

285
00:18:11,567 --> 00:18:14,333
Dad, she had difficulty
breathing the other day

286
00:18:14,467 --> 00:18:16,100
Jeffrey...

287
00:18:16,233 --> 00:18:17,933
I told you that...

288
00:18:18,067 --> 00:18:19,467
I went up...

289
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:22,667
to the library because
I'm going to get a book.

290
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:25,067
Why did you have to go upstairs?

291
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:27,733
I told you I'd get
the book for you.

292
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:30,700
I can't hear it anymore.

293
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:33,967
Love, how are you
doing there?

294
00:18:34,100 --> 00:18:36,967
I'm still getting used to it.

295
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:38,833
I've only been here for weeks.

296
00:18:38,967 --> 00:18:40,400
But I want to go home already.

297
00:18:42,067 --> 00:18:45,667
<i>I just think that
I'm doing this for you.</i>

298
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,533
<i> Especially for you, Andeng.</i>

299
00:18:47,667 --> 00:18:49,533
<i> I want you to get better soon.</i>

300
00:18:50,133 --> 00:18:52,633
<i>So that you can live much,
much longer.</i>

301
00:18:53,667 --> 00:18:56,133
<i>Just now, I'm feeling
motivated again.</i>

302
00:18:57,633 --> 00:18:58,767
I miss you, Dad.

303
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:01,333
I miss you, too, Dad.

304
00:19:05,133 --> 00:19:07,500
<i>I miss you so much, too,
my children.</i>

305
00:19:20,033 --> 00:19:21,567
How are you doing?

306
00:19:22,533 --> 00:19:25,167
Yes, just be patient.

307
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:27,233
Peace be with you.

308
00:19:27,367 --> 00:19:29,967
Put it a little lower.

309
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,567
You know it's not that easy.

310
00:19:37,700 --> 00:19:40,333
Put it a little lower.
Go, a little lower.

311
00:19:40,467 --> 00:19:42,533
I hope you do something for now.

312
00:19:44,533 --> 00:19:45,500
Hazel!

313
00:19:45,633 --> 00:19:47,867
You know that we don't have...

314
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:49,267
Hazel!

315
00:19:56,633 --> 00:19:58,367
Manuel!

316
00:19:59,667 --> 00:20:01,000
You're hurt.

317
00:20:02,300 --> 00:20:03,667
Wait.

318
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:05,333
Wait.

319
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:17,933
Please bring patient Quarashi
to the x-ray room first,

320
00:20:19,667 --> 00:20:22,467
before you endorse him
to the ward.

321
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:24,067
Where's the request for x-ray?

322
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:25,700
Here.

323
00:20:51,933 --> 00:20:53,067
Hey.

324
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:54,867
Why do you look at Manuel
like that?

325
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:02,567
Why did he save me?

326
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:04,533
We're not that close.

327
00:21:05,667 --> 00:21:07,767
My exes wouldn't even do that.

328
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:12,333
So, the damsel in distress

329
00:21:12,467 --> 00:21:16,200
has finally met
her prince charming?

330
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:18,467
What are you talking about?

331
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:19,700
No offense,

332
00:21:20,133 --> 00:21:23,300
but come on, Alice.

333
00:21:23,433 --> 00:21:24,533
I'm a nurse.

334
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:27,800
Manuel is...

335
00:21:27,933 --> 00:21:29,233
a janitor.

336
00:21:29,967 --> 00:21:30,667
So?

337
00:21:31,567 --> 00:21:32,833
Manuel is a good person.

338
00:21:32,967 --> 00:21:35,933
Hardworking, courageous,
he even saved you.

339
00:21:36,067 --> 00:21:37,200
What else could you ask for?

340
00:21:37,333 --> 00:21:38,433
I already have a boyfriend.

341
00:21:38,567 --> 00:21:39,433
But still.

342
00:21:39,567 --> 00:21:41,467
Even I did,
if I'm not married,

343
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:42,833
he has a chance with me.

344
00:21:43,767 --> 00:21:45,167
Come on.

345
00:21:45,300 --> 00:21:46,433
He's married.

346
00:21:47,467 --> 00:21:49,333
That's what Abel said.

347
00:21:49,933 --> 00:21:53,867
But I heard that he's only
living with that woman.

348
00:21:54,533 --> 00:21:57,067
So, they're not married.

349
00:21:57,867 --> 00:22:00,067
They're not a married couple

350
00:22:09,267 --> 00:22:10,633
Love, thank you.

351
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:15,100
Okay, Love. I love you, too.

352
00:22:15,267 --> 00:22:17,067
Cool! Dad remembered!

353
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:19,633
Yes! I have
coloring materials now!

354
00:22:20,833 --> 00:22:23,600
Look. Yes, he sent a lot.

355
00:22:23,733 --> 00:22:25,067
There's chocolate!

356
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:26,467
This is a lot!

357
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:27,600
- Mom.
- Oh?

358
00:22:27,733 --> 00:22:29,167
Dad's letter.

359
00:22:29,300 --> 00:22:30,500
Let me see. Give me what's mine.

360
00:22:30,633 --> 00:22:31,533
Maybe I have one.

361
00:22:31,667 --> 00:22:32,733
Where's mine?
Here's yours.

362
00:22:33,867 --> 00:22:35,167
Jeffrey, look.

363
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:37,367
Dad wrote me a letter.

364
00:22:40,567 --> 00:22:41,600
Andeng?

365
00:22:42,300 --> 00:22:43,467
- I'm okay.
- Dear.

366
00:22:44,433 --> 00:22:45,800
Dear.

367
00:22:45,933 --> 00:22:47,233
Always jumping around.

368
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:49,167
You know you're ill.

369
00:22:49,333 --> 00:22:51,067
- How would I know?
- Jeffrey,

370
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:52,633
stop lecturing your sister.

371
00:22:52,767 --> 00:22:54,767
Give her some water. Come on.

372
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:56,100
Jeffrey.

373
00:22:56,233 --> 00:22:57,200
Thank you.

374
00:23:02,233 --> 00:23:05,200
I got excited when I saw
the package dad sent us.

375
00:23:05,333 --> 00:23:07,900
I wish dad were here.

376
00:23:08,033 --> 00:23:10,200
So we'd be happier.

377
00:23:10,333 --> 00:23:13,300
Yes, I talked to him.

378
00:23:13,433 --> 00:23:14,900
He sent this to us,

379
00:23:15,033 --> 00:23:18,333
so we don't need to borrow
your Aunt Paz's phone.

380
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:23,500
My dear children,
your dad had an accident.

381
00:23:23,667 --> 00:23:26,300
- Oh, no.
- What happened?

382
00:23:26,433 --> 00:23:30,267
He got hurt
while helping a nurse.

383
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:32,367
He's doing okay now.

384
00:23:32,500 --> 00:23:33,767
So you don't have to worry.

385
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:38,300
Why did he help the nurse?

386
00:23:38,433 --> 00:23:39,400
Who is she?

387
00:23:41,467 --> 00:23:42,467
Her name's Hazel.

388
00:23:43,567 --> 00:23:44,633
His friend.

389
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:50,633
Mom is jealous.

390
00:23:50,767 --> 00:23:52,567
Of course not.

391
00:23:52,700 --> 00:23:54,100
- No.
- Mom, it's too obvious...

392
00:23:54,233 --> 00:23:56,833
No, I trust your father.

393
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:58,300
It's not easy.

394
00:23:58,433 --> 00:24:00,333
He's so far away.

395
00:24:00,467 --> 00:24:03,433
He's with others instead of me.

396
00:24:04,533 --> 00:24:06,400
Even though, your face
says it all, Mom.

397
00:24:06,533 --> 00:24:07,533
You're jealous.

398
00:24:07,667 --> 00:24:08,900
You really are jealous.

399
00:24:09,033 --> 00:24:11,167
- Jealous!
- You'll wake Coleen up.

400
00:24:11,300 --> 00:24:12,033
Stop.

401
00:24:12,167 --> 00:24:13,133
Sorry. Sorry.

402
00:24:24,733 --> 00:24:25,800
You're pregnant?

403
00:24:29,233 --> 00:24:30,733
What did Jojo say?

404
00:24:32,467 --> 00:24:34,633
Nothing.

405
00:24:34,767 --> 00:24:37,633
That jerk is not answering
my calls anymore.

406
00:24:37,767 --> 00:24:41,000
My god, friend!
That's a problem!

407
00:24:41,133 --> 00:24:44,500
You know it's a crime here
to get pregnant out of wedlock.

408
00:24:45,933 --> 00:24:48,500
What if you go back
to the Philippines for now?

409
00:24:48,633 --> 00:24:49,933
Stay there until you give birth

410
00:24:51,633 --> 00:24:53,567
What about my family?

411
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:57,100
How can I support them?

412
00:24:58,167 --> 00:25:00,267
What happens if your baby bump
starts to show?

413
00:25:01,367 --> 00:25:03,900
Who will you present
as the father?

414
00:25:14,833 --> 00:25:16,600
- Please come!
- There they are!

415
00:25:16,733 --> 00:25:18,133
- Oh!
- Honey!

416
00:25:18,267 --> 00:25:19,733
- Hi!
- I fetched your guests.

417
00:25:19,867 --> 00:25:21,933
- Hi, Charles!
- What are you?

418
00:25:22,067 --> 00:25:24,233
- Happy birthday!
- Yes, come in!

419
00:25:24,367 --> 00:25:25,700
Thank you.

420
00:25:25,833 --> 00:25:27,567
You shouldn't have brought
something.

421
00:25:27,700 --> 00:25:29,267
Please put it here.

422
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:30,867
Thank you.
Thank you so much, guys.

423
00:25:31,933 --> 00:25:33,200
Thank you!

424
00:25:33,333 --> 00:25:34,933
Sit down for now.

425
00:25:35,100 --> 00:25:36,967
Okay, guys.
Make yourself at home.

426
00:25:37,100 --> 00:25:38,967
As long as you're in our house,
you can do as you please.

427
00:25:39,100 --> 00:25:40,533
Got it?

428
00:25:40,667 --> 00:25:41,700
What do you think of these,
Honey?

429
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,267
Thank you so much, Honey.

430
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:47,033
You made me so happy.

431
00:25:47,167 --> 00:25:48,133
I love it.

432
00:25:52,433 --> 00:25:53,867
Okay, I'm going to take

433
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,800
- a quick shower.
- Okay.

434
00:25:55,933 --> 00:25:57,767
Okay, guys. Make yourself
at home, okay?

435
00:26:01,967 --> 00:26:02,900
Hey.

436
00:26:03,033 --> 00:26:04,267
- Yes?
- You.

437
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:06,200
You're so lucky to have Charles.

438
00:26:06,333 --> 00:26:07,467
He seems to be
so in love with you.

439
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:09,767
Don't worry.

440
00:26:09,900 --> 00:26:12,633
You'll find someone
like him, too.

441
00:26:14,967 --> 00:26:16,100
I think I found him.

442
00:26:17,567 --> 00:26:20,300
Or more on...

443
00:26:20,433 --> 00:26:22,533
like someone who can help me
with my baby.

444
00:26:26,100 --> 00:26:28,467
Manuel, please answer my call.

445
00:26:29,100 --> 00:26:30,667
Manuel, answer the call.

446
00:26:32,033 --> 00:26:33,733
What happened?

447
00:26:33,867 --> 00:26:35,200
You were so drunk last night.

448
00:26:35,333 --> 00:26:37,533
You insisted on kissing me.

449
00:26:37,667 --> 00:26:39,600
I didn't want it but...

450
00:26:39,733 --> 00:26:41,300
but there's nothing I could do.

451
00:26:41,433 --> 00:26:43,367
Your wife's been calling you.

452
00:26:43,533 --> 00:26:46,267
Paz is even nagging me!
You can't be reached!

453
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:47,467
What happened?

454
00:26:48,033 --> 00:26:49,167
Why did Felma call?

455
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:50,667
It's because of Andrea!

456
00:26:50,900 --> 00:26:52,033
Where's Manuel?

457
00:26:52,167 --> 00:26:53,867
He left his phone.

458
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:55,300
He was here earlier.

459
00:26:55,433 --> 00:26:57,533
He's soliciting money
for your daughter.

460
00:26:57,667 --> 00:26:58,567
Ouch!

461
00:26:58,700 --> 00:26:59,600
Let go of me!

462
00:26:59,733 --> 00:27:00,700
- What the...
- Don't ever talk

463
00:27:00,833 --> 00:27:01,867
to my wife again!
Do you understand?

464
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:03,133
Are you scared
that she'll find out

465
00:27:03,267 --> 00:27:04,733
what happened between us?

466
00:27:04,867 --> 00:27:06,900
It only happened once.
It will never happen again!

467
00:27:07,700 --> 00:27:09,333
On the day of your departure,

468
00:27:09,467 --> 00:27:11,233
you'll get your passport.

469
00:27:11,367 --> 00:27:12,700
Thank you, Ma'am.

470
00:27:12,833 --> 00:27:14,400
I can finally go home.

471
00:27:14,533 --> 00:27:16,733
You're going home?
Why all of a sudden?

472
00:27:16,900 --> 00:27:18,567
Don't you want me to go home?

473
00:27:18,700 --> 00:27:20,067
Of course, I do.

474
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:22,300
I couldn't wait
to see you and the kids.

475
00:27:22,433 --> 00:27:23,767
Me, too, my Love.
